    "biography": "<p>The Manscorpion, a vile blend of man and scorpion, prowls caverns, deserts, and mountains, its human-like torso atop the segmented body of a giant arachnid. Driven by malice, it roams any climate, ambushing intruders and raiding desert human enclaves for sustenance.</p><p>It wields a huge pole arm (dealing [[/r 3d6 #Pole arm damage]]) or other weapons, paired with a venomous tail strike ([[/r 1d10 #Tail damage]] + poison, save vs. poison or die, paralysis for [[/r 1d8-1 #Rounds paralyzed]] even if saved). Immune to its kin’s venom, it strikes with deadly intent.</p><p>Intelligent yet hostile, bands of [[/r 1d8 #Manscorpions wandering]] or lairs of [[/r 2d10 #Manscorpions in lair]] hoard rich treasures, their chaotic nature spurning alliances save with giant scorpions. A relentless foe (HD 8, XP 1750), it destroys all unlike itself.<br><b>Terrain:</b> Cavern, Desert, Mountain</p>",
